Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual inputs (RGB images) and uses convolutional layers for encoding. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with forecasting human motion, which is relevant to robotics applications. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a model for trajectory forecasting using deep learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with predicting future trajectories, which is a common task in AI applications. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) in the form of the paper title and abstract.
